@ruipacheco Just returning works for assertions directly inside a test case, but assertions are specifically intended to support nested function, e.g. this
```cpp
void check_bits(uint32_t val) {
    REQUIRE(val & 1 == 1);
    REQUIRE(val & 2 == 0);
    REQUIRE(val & 4 == 4);
}

TEST_CASE("foo") {
    uint32_t val = getval();
    check_bits(val);
}
```

the only way to support this is via exceptions, or exception-like mechanism. This leads to the problem where the only way to support `-fno-exceptions` is to hard abort on failed assertion, which is... suboptimal for a test framework.

Bubble up error codes?

